  "texts": [
    "The recommended wearable biosensors are those that measure HR to study user anxiety, and EDA and respiration devices to complement it.",
    "Once again, Desktop 6DOF is the recommended HMD.",
    "The second situation is to help patients to control the virtual environment through motor imagery (e.g., Winter et al. 2021).",
    "These applications are often used by patients undergoing rehabilitation for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (e.g., McClinton et al. 2019), strokes (e.g., Spicer et al. 2017), paralysis (e.g., Qidwai et al. 2019), and other illnesses causing user immobility.",
    "In such contexts, EEG wearable sensors are always used, because they transform brain waves into movements within the virtual environment, so there is no need for physical movements."
  ],
